fmNQY=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing serialization coverage**\\n\\nI’m pondering whether there's no coverage related to the test method name. Perhaps I could generate a serialized form where `BCDilithiumPrivateKey.readObject` utilizes `in.readObject()` to return a `BCDilithiumPrivateKey`. It seems the custom for BCBIKE enforces nesting. Still, the call site is important! I wonder if the instrumentation counts dynamic access when `ObjectOutputStream.writeObject` sees `BCDilithiumPrivateKey`. The problem is that writing byte arrays typically avoids reflective serialization. So, to ensure coverage for reflection in `ObjectOutputStream#writeObject`, I might need to alter arguments for reflection to occur.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Sorting out serialization issues**\\n\\nI'm running into an issue with a missing object, but it's not BCDilithium. Maybe I should consider using serialPersistentFields? No, that doesn't seem right. I think I need to add `serialVersionUID` to the holder. Restoring a custom stream might be a good approach, and possibly keeping a direct test as well. Since the previous custom with BCDilithium had no coverage, maybe the holder might be useful here. I'll also need to import IOException and Serializable before implementing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_TRu1Fbrf5moLeIRjyjARdtiR|fc_04b5302d059abbec016a261ac7fe3481968b978f0f92eac988", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCDilithiumPrivateKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\n\n", "newText": "import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\n\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static byte[] serialize(BCDilithiumPrivateKey privateKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream byteOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(byteOutputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(privateKey);\n        }\n        return byteOutputStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCDilithiumPrivateKey deserialize(byte[] serialized) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectInputStream = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized))) {\n            return (BCDilithiumPrivateKey)objectInputStream.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static byte[] serialize(BCDilithiumPrivateKey privateKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream byteOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream =\n                new EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(byteOutputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(privateKey);\n            assertEquals(1, objectOutputStream.replacedEncodedKeys);\n        }\n        return byteOutputStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCDilithiumPrivateKey deserialize(byte[] serialized) throws Exception {\n        try (EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream objectInputStream =\n                new EncodedPrivateKeyResolvingObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized))) {\n            BCDilithiumPrivateKey restored = (BCDilithiumPrivateKey)objectInputStream.readObject();\n            assertEquals(1, objectInputStream.resolvedEncodedKeys);\n            return restored;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private int replacedEncodedKeys;\n\n        private EncodedPrivateKeyReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream)\n                throws IOException {\n            super(outputStream);\n    